  <h1>
   gxc_start_movie_recording
  </h1>
  This function is used to start recording your challenge on GXC. You specify the width, height and frame rate of the recording, and a boolean for whether the audio should be recorded or not.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gxc_start_movie_recording(width, height, fps, record_audio);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <colgroup>
    <col/>
    <col/>
    <col/>
   </colgroup>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      width
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The width of the recording
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      height
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The height of the recording
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      fps
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Real
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The frame rate (frames-per-second) of the recording
     </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      record_audio
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
        Boolean
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      Whether audio should be recorded (
      <span>
       true
      </span>
      ) or not (
      <span>
       false
      </span>
      )
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">N/A
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gxc_start_movie_recording(320, 240, 4, false);
</code></pre>
  This will start a video recording at a resolution of 320x240 at 4 frames-per-second, without any audio being recorded.
